body:
@LukaszRozmej  On Windows, I've fixed it by removing `MemoryHint` option to disable built-in memory allocation and manually specify the `Db` options as follows:

```json
"Db": {
    "CacheIndexAndFilterBlocks": true,
    "BlockCacheSize": 81920000000,
    "WriteBufferSize": 51920000000,
    "WriteBufferNumber": 1
  },
```

As a fun fact, the Archive Node performance actually increased from `0.23` bps to `0.94` bps as I expected and reported in #2885
